Saman Rawcliffe lost all control of her body and crashed her car last May . 
  The mother-of-two was shaking uncontrollably in the days after the accident . 
  She was diagnosed with the rare condition functional neurological disorder last September . 
  The 40-year-old is confined to her home and has to take 32 different drugs a day . 
  She lost control of the bladder and is now unable to walk . 
  Mrs Rawcliffe said: 'I have no feeling in my bladder'